<Content>Pleasantly surprised!!! We stayed at the Emporio Reforma for nine nights recently and we were pleasantly surprised. We based the selection totally on location (Reforma is the main blvd in Mx Cty). We felt very safe, we even walked home nightly from Zona Rosa at 3 AM with no problems. We were very pleased with the services of the Hotel Car Service. Our driver, Alejandro - ALEX - was very pleasant and proved invaluable with our sightseeing and general information on the history of Mexico City. We hired Alex to drive us for two full days and he ensured we were taken care of at tourist sites and introduced us to some great places to eat. He adjusted his hours to suit our needs. The hotel was very clean, the staff friendly (although very few were bilingual but it gave us a chance to put our Spanish into use). The decor of the hotel is European and very nice. We ate breakfast most mornings at the hotel and felt it was good value for the money. The hotel is central to all and we plan on staying there again in the near future. 
