<Author>VerdeRosa
<Content>Stylish and friendly We just got back from a 4-night stay at the Emporio Reforma. We like smaller contemporary style hotels and the Emporio was exactly what we were looking for. It has been recently remodeled so everything is clean and new. The cheaper rooms ($70 plus taxes per night) are very small (we knew that ahead of time from reading Trip Advisor reviews) but very tastefully decorated. The bed was very comfortable.. not too hard not too soft. Even though it's situated more in a business area, we liked the location as it's within a 15- 20 minutes to walk to the historic center, Zona Rosa and Chapultepec Park. The nearest metro stop (Juarez or Hidalgo) was about a 10-minute walk. We felt very safe even at night as there were lots of police around. I agree with other reviewers that the staff didn't seem too knowledgeable about tourist attractions so we relied mostly on guidebooks and tourist office for information. We had read about overcharges on taxi rides to the airport from hotels and were pleased that the taxi ordered for us by the Emporio charged us $15 which was very fair. Breakfast and a dinner at the hotel restaurant were quite good. We also had good classic Mexican food at the Cafe de Tacuba in the historic area (nice casual ambience) and great contemporary mexican-international at the Orsai (Avenue de la Paz) in San Angel. Overall a very good experience. 
