<Content>A little disappointing My husband and I just came back from a 7 nights' stay in Mexico city, and stayed in this hotel for the duration of our trip. Having read some of the reviews before we booked, we were expecting the hotel to be a lot better than we experienced. All in all it was okay. Let me start with the positives: The staff were all very friendly and helpful, and were extrememely patient with us with our poor spanish. The room was clean and modern. The breakfast buffet was nice and varied, but at 90 pesos a person, you're better off finding a small cafe in the area. The location was not bad, a great plus was that it was close to the Turibus stop. However, it was a good long walk to the nearest metro stop. Now for the negatives: even though we booked a double room, we were put into what was the smallest room I have ever been in. The bed was about the size of a full sized bed, barely big enough for 2 grown people to sleep - and it took up most of the space in the room. The closet was so small, that once we'd each hung up 2 items of clothing, it was full. The bathroom was probably the size of any other hotel's closet. To say that the room was cramped is an understatement. To make matters worse, when we asked to switch rooms, we were told that we would have to pay more! Then we were only given one small bottle of water, even though it was a double occupancy room. For what we paid, I would have expected a bit more. And so next time, we plan to stay elsewhere. 
